content:
Show Customers an Estimated Wait Time in the Messaging Window

Automatically tell customers how many minutes they have to wait before being connected to an agent. Build customer trust by setting expectations.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Messaging for In-App and Messaging for Web channels. Not available in Standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel.

To set up this feature:

Customize Application
Modify Metadata Through Metadata API Functions

Conditions that must be met to show Estimated wait time include:

* You activated Estimated Wait Time.
* Agents accepted at least 10 messaging requests in the last 10 minutes in the corresponding queue.

To trigger estimated wait time, the Routing Type field for your deployment in Messaging Settings must be set to Omni-Queue or Omni-Flow with a selected flow that routes to a queue. If the estimated wait time is less than 1 minute, we round it up to 1 minute.

From Setup, enter Messaging Settings and select Edit. Click Show estimated wait time and Save your changes.
title: Service Cloud: Estimated Wait Time in Messaging Window
